======================================================================
PART 5: MUSICAL INTERVALS AND THE PYTHAGOREAN COMMA
======================================================================

The musical scale is built from KEY₁ and KEY₂:

  Unison                    1          = 1/1             (   0.00 cents)
  Minor 2nd                 256/243    = KEY₁⁸/KEY₂⁵     (  90.22 cents)
  Major 2nd (whole tone)    9/8        = KEY₂²/KEY₁³     ( 203.91 cents)
  Minor 3rd                 32/27      = KEY₁⁵/KEY₂³     ( 294.13 cents)
  Major 3rd                 81/64      = KEY₂⁴/KEY₁⁶     ( 407.82 cents)
  Perfect 4th               4/3        = KEY₁²/KEY₂      ( 498.04 cents)
  Tritone (aug 4th)         729/512    = KEY₂⁶/KEY₁⁹     ( 611.73 cents)
  Perfect 5th               3/2        = KEY₂/KEY₁       ( 701.96 cents)
  Minor 6th                 128/81     = KEY₁⁷/KEY₂⁴     ( 792.18 cents)
  Major 6th                 27/16      = KEY₂³/KEY₁⁴     ( 905.87 cents)
  Minor 7th                 16/9       = KEY₁⁴/KEY₂²     ( 996.09 cents)
  Major 7th                 243/128    = KEY₂⁵/KEY₁⁷     (1109.78 cents)
  Octave                    2          = KEY₁            (1200.00 cents)

  Pythagorean comma: 3¹²/2¹⁹ = 531441/524288 ≈ 1.0136432648
  = KEY₂¹²/KEY₁¹⁹
  12 = h(E₆) = h(F₄)
  19 = h(E₇)+1 = dim(E₇)/rank(E₇)

  The Pythagorean comma = KEY₂^h(E₆) / KEY₁^(dim(E₇)/rank(E₇))
  TWO Lie-theoretic quantities determine the musical comma!

  12 perfect fifths = (3/2)¹² = 531441/4096
  7 octaves = 2⁷ = 128
  Difference = (3/2)¹² - 2⁷ = 1.746338
  12 = h(E₆) fifths overshoot 7 = rank(E₇) octaves
  by exactly the Pythagorean comma ≈ 23.46 cents

======================================================================
PART 6: THE INFORMATION-THEORETIC VIEW
======================================================================

  Partition of [1,30) into exponents (8) and non-exponents (21):
  p(exponent) = 8/29 ≈ 0.275862
  p(tournament) = 21/29 ≈ 0.724138
  Binary entropy H = 0.849751 bits

  Alternate: 8 totatives out of 30:
  p = 8/30 = 4/15 ≈ 0.266667
  H = 0.836641 bits

  Information content of 5 exceptional groups:
  log₂(5) = 2.321928 bits ≈ KEY₁+KEY₂ - 1 - 1/3...
  = 2.32 bits

  Tournament polynomial f(z) = z² - 5z + 6:
  Has 2 roots → 1 bit to specify which root
  But root MULTIPLICITIES carry more information:
  z=2 (mult 1), z=3 (mult 1): 1 bit
  The polynomial is SEPARABLE: discriminant = 1 ≠ 0
  Separability ⟺ the two keys are DISTINCT

======================================================================
PART 7: ONE PAGE OF THE UNIVERSE
======================================================================


THE (2,3,5) UNIVERSE — A ONE-PAGE SUMMARY

AXIOM: z² - 5z + 6 = 0 has roots KEY₁ = 2, KEY₂ = 3.

FROM THIS SINGLE EQUATION:

ARITHMETIC
  Product 2·3 = 6 = h(G₂)
  Sum 2+3 = 5 = # exceptional Lie groups = # Platonic solids
  Triple product 2·3·5 = 30 = h(E₈)
  φ(30) = τ(30) = 8 = 2³ = rank(E₈)

RECURRENCES
  k-nacci → 2 (geometric rate 1/2)
  Weight-2 k-nacci → 3 (general: weight w → w+1)
  a(n) = 5a(n-1) - 6a(n-2) generates ALL sequences A·2ⁿ+B·3ⁿ
  Corner pieces: 3ⁿ-2ⁿ = 0, 1, 5, 19, 65, 211, ...

GEOMETRY
  (2,3,5) = last spherical triple → icosahedron/dodecahedron
  V(icos)·V(dodec) = 12·20 = 240 = #roots(E₈)
  30-edge trinity: icos, dodec, Petersen complement
  All have |Aut| = 120 = 5! = |S₅|

THE PETERSEN GRAPH K(5,2)
  10 vertices = 2·5, 15 edges = C(6,2)
  Eigenvalues {3, 1, -2} with multiplicities {1, 5, 4}
  Independence polynomial: I_k/C(5,k) = {1, 2, 3, 3, 1}
  ω·α = 2·4 = 8 = rank(E₈)
  P(Petersen, 3) = 120 = |BI| = |Aut|
  6 perfect matchings = h(G₂)

SIEVE
  Multiples of {2,3,5} in [1,30): tournament theory (21 numbers)
  Coprime to 30: Lie exponents (8 numbers = totatives)
  E₈ exponents = {1} ∪ {primes in (5,30)}
  The two theories partition ALL integers

LIE THEORY
  dim(g) = rank(g)·(h(g)+1) universal
  h+1 = {7, 13, 13, 19, 31} = {M₃, 2²+3², 2²+3², 3³-2³, M₅}
  E₈ positive roots: 120 = |BI| = |S₅|
  h(E₈)/h(G₂) = 5, h(E₇)/h(E₆) = 3/2

MUSIC
  Perfect 5th = 3/2 = KEY₂/KEY₁
  Whole tone = 9/8 = KEY₂²/KEY₁³
  Pythagorean comma = 3¹²/2¹⁹ = KEY₂^h(E₆)/KEY₁^(h(E₇)+1)
  12 fifths ≈ 7 octaves (off by the comma)

THE BOUNDARY
  1/2 + 1/3 + 1/5 = 31/30 > 1: E₈ EXISTS
  1/2 + 1/3 + 1/7 = 41/42 < 1: E₉ DOES NOT
  Excess = 1/30 = 1/h(E₈): the last gap before the boundary
  f(10) = 56 = T(6): the polynomial at the boundary encodes T(6)

THE MARKOV-LIKE IDENTITY
  2² + 3² + 5² - 2·3·5 = 8 = rank(E₈)
  a² + b² + c² - abc = rank of the maximal exceptional group

